[4] Denmark, wild birds, update
Date: Thu, 30 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Danish Veterinary and Food Administration's website, accessed 30
Mar 2006 [edited]
<http://www.uk.foedevarestyrelsen.dk/AnimalHealth/Avian_influenza/Latest_news/forside.htm>

On 30 Mar 2006 the Danish Veterinary and Food Research Institute detected
high pathogenic avian influenza (H5) in a tufted duck (_Aythya fuligula_)
[picture <http://www.stanford.edu/~petelat1/photos/tudu-1.jpg>] found dead
on Kegnaes in the southern part of Jutland.
The Danish Veterinary and Food Administration is implementing measures in
accordance with Commission Decision 2006/115/EC including establishing a
protection and surveillance zone. Kegnaes is located near Sonderborg, and
surveillance zone already established on 29 Mar 2006 is therefore not
changed, but a new protection zone has been established.
On 29 Mar 2006 the Danish Veterinary and Food Research Institute detected
high pathogenic avian influenza (H5) in a common buzzard (_Buteo buteo_)
[picture <http://www.internatura.org/guias/rapaces/bb1_g.jpg>] found dead
near the town of Sonderborg in the southern part of Jutland.
The Danish Veterinary and Food Administration is implementing measures in
accordance with Commission Decision 2006/115/EC including establishing a
protection and surveillance zone.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Danish reporting of avian influenza, as also shown in their above website,
is clear and swift. The notifications are accompanied by a map which is
updated every day.
A European map on avian influenza in wild birds is available at the EU
website, which is also updated on a daily basis:
<http://europa.eu.int/comm/food/animal/diseases/adns/index_en.htm#>. - Mod.AS]
